<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Bankers cut holding in IBC to 8%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
International Business Communications (Holdings), the publishing, conference
and training group, has been informed that Williams de Broe, its broker, has
agreed to acquire 4.48m shares in the company from certain of the group's
bankers.
The agreement follows the allotment of new ordinary shares to be issued
pursuant to the placing, open offer and conversion of debenture stock and
the consolidation of the existing ordinaries.
Of those shares, which will represent 11.5 per cent of the enlarged and
consolidated share capital, 4.28m have been placed with institutional and
other investors.
As a result of the acquisition and placing, the aggregate shareholding of
the banks will be reduced to 8 per cent.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>International Business Communications (Holdings).
    Williams de Broe.
</CO>
