<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Forte seeks buyer for Harvester chain
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SKAPINKER, Leisure Industries Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
FORTE, the hotels group, confirmed yesterday that it had begun to seek
buyers for its Harvester restaurant chain.
If no suitable buyer is found by the autumn, the group might either extend
the brand, currently based predominantly in the south-east of England,
throughout the UK or put the business into a joint venture.
Forte is believed to be looking for a price in excess of the Pounds 120m
mentioned in some reports.
It is also thought to be interested in selling its stake in the UK Kentucky
Fried Chicken business.
This is run in a joint venture with Pepsico, which is seen as the most
likely buyer of the Forte stake.
</TEXT>
