FT  20 JUL 93 / UK Company News: Yorks Water buys third finance leasing
company
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
   YORKSHIRE WATER, the Leeds
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
based water and sewage company, is acquiring its third finance leasing
company as part of its ongoing treasury management programme.
The company announced yesterday that it had acquired JHSW Leasing (9), a
wholly owned subsidiary of J Henry Schroder Wagg. The company, to be renamed
Yorkshire Water Third Finance, has a portfolio of finance leases, with lease
rentals receivable of Pounds 65.5m.
