<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUL 93 / Full list of 10 alleged crimes: Substantial changes made to
indictment
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The full list of charges against the six defendants are:
1. Credit Suisse
That Kevin Maxwell, Larry Trachtenberg, Robert Bunn and Albert Fuller,
between July 1 1990 and December 6 1991, conspired together and with Robert
Maxwell to defraud Credit Suisse ('the bank') by falsely representing that
Robert Maxwell Group plc (RMG) (formerly known as Mirror Group plc) was the
beneficial owner of shares of Berlitz International Incorporated belonging
to Macmillan Incorporated and shares belonging to First Tokyo Index Trust
plc delivered to the bank as security under the terms of an agreement, dated
September 7 1990, between the bank and RMG for a loan facility of Pounds
50m.
2. Baverische Vereinsbank
That Kevin Maxwell, Robert Bunn, Albert Fuller and Ian Maxwell, between July
16 1990 and February 29 1991, conspired together and with Robert Maxwell to
defraud Bayerische Vereinsbank AG ('the bank') by falsely representing to
the bank that Mirror Group plc (subsequently known as Robert Maxwell Group
plc) or Pergamon Holdings Ltd was the beneficial owner of shares delivered
to the bank as security under the terms of an agreement, dated July 30 1990,
between the bank and Mirror Group plc for a loan facility of Pounds 25m.
3. Swiss Bank Corporation
That Kevin Maxwell and Robert Bunn between May 1 1991 and December 10 1991
conspired together and with Robert Maxwell to defraud Swiss Bank Corporation
('the bank') by selling shares belonging to First Tokyo Index Trust plc
knowing that such sale was contrary to representations and warranties given
to the bank.
4. Scitex Corporation Ltd
That Kevin Maxwell between July 3 1991 and December 10 1991 conspired
together with Robert Maxwell to defraud the trustees and beneficiaries of
the pension schemes that participated in the Common Investment Fund managed
by Bishopsgate Investment Management Ltd by: (i) falsely representing that
Robert Maxwell Group plc was able to pay Bishopsgate Investment Management
Ltd for 5,400,000 shares in Scitex Corporation Ltd; (ii) selling the shares
and using the proceeds of sale to the benefit of Robert Maxwell Group plc
knowing that there was a risk that it would not be able to pay Bishopsgate
Investment Management Ltd the sum to which it was entitled.
5. Independent fund managers
That Kevin Maxwell and Larry Trachtenberg between September 18 1991 and
December 10 1991 conspired together and with Robert Maxwell to defraud the
trustees and beneficiaries of the Mirror Group Pension Scheme and the AGB
Pension Scheme by using shares which formed part of the assets of the
schemes (and which were, on September 18 1991, managed by Lloyds Investment
Management Ltd, Thornton Investment Management Ltd, Lazard Freres, and
Morgan Grenfell Investment Management Ltd) as collateral to secure credit
facilities granted by Credit Suisse and Swiss Volksbank to Robert Maxwell
Group plc knowing that there was a risk that Robert Maxwell Group plc would
default on the credit facilities and the shares would be forfeit.
6. MGN
That Kevin Maxwell and Michael Stoney, between August 1 1991 and December 3
1991, conspired together and with Robert Maxwell to defraud MGN Ltd by
obtaining from Bankers Trust Company in the name of MGN Ltd a revolving
credit facility in the sum of Pounds 50m and using the proceeds of the same
for purposes other than the purposes of MGN Ltd.
7. MGN
That Michael Stoney, between October 21 1991 and December 2 1991,
dishonestly falsified a document required for an accounting purpose, namely
the general ledger of MGN Ltd, by omitting or concurring in the omitting
from the general ledger a material particular, namely the receipt on October
21 1991 of Pounds 50m from Bankers Trust Company.
8. MGN
That Michael Stoney, between October 21 1991 and December 2 1991,
dishonestly falsified a document required for an accounting purpose, namely
a group financial report by omitting or concurring in the omitting from the
said group financial report a material particular, namely the liability of
MGN Ltd to Bankers Trust Company in respect of the revolving facility in the
sum of Pounds 50m.
9. Swiss Volksbank
That Kevin Maxwell, Larry Trachtenberg, Robert Bunn and Ian Maxwell, between
November 4 and 21 1991 conspired together to defraud the Swiss Volksbank
('the bank') by falsely representing: (i) that Robert Maxwell Group plc was
then the recorded and beneficial owner of 2.4m shares in Berlitz
International Incorporated ('the shares') to be delivered to the bank as
security for the granting of a loan facility of USDollars 35,506,000 to
Robert Maxwell Group Trading plc ('the loan'); (ii) that Robert Maxwell
Group plc then had marketable title to the shares; (iii) that it was
intended that the loan would be repaid to the bank from the proceeds of sale
to Fukutake Publishing of shares of common stock in Berlitz International
Incorporated owned by Robert Maxwell Group plc.
10. Teva
That Kevin Maxwell, Larry Trachtenberg, Robert Bunn and Ian Maxwell between
November 5 and 21 1991, conspired together to defraud the trustees and
beneficiaries of the pension schemes that participated in the Common
Investment Fund managed by Bishopsgate Investment Management Ltd by granting
to National Westminster Bank plc a charge over 25,196,228 shares in Teva
Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd, which formed part of the schemes' assets, as
security for credit facilities granted by National Westminster Bank plc to
Robert Maxwell Group plc knowing that there was a risk that Robert Maxwell
Group plc would default on the said credit facilities and the shares would
be forfeit.
</TEXT>
