<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JUL 93 / Sugar legal move is adjourned
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A LEGAL move by Mr Alan Sugar, the Tottenham Hotspur chairman, to force Mr
Terry Venables, the ousted chief executive, to pay money into court before
Mr Venables attempts a buy-out was adjourned yesterday until Thursday next
week.
Mr Sugar is seeking a High Court order requiring Edennote, Mr Venables'
company, to put up security for costs to cover all or part of Spurs' legal
expenses in the event of the buy-out bid failing.
