</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Treuhand agency for restructuring and privatising eastern German
industry has reversed its decision to close a loss-making potash mine, in a
move to ensure its radical plan to merge western and eastern Germany's
potash sector is implemented, writes Judy Dempsey in Berlin.
The decision to reprieve 700 jobs at the Bischofferoder mine in Thuringia
follows a two-week hunger strike by 47 employees.
The Treuhand and the state government propose that the mine should stay open
temporarily to save jobs until 1995.
