FT  19 JUL 93 / Observer: Class question
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Is a privileged upbringing still the best route to the top in Britain?
No, according to a survey of 130 headhunters by the Executive Grapevine
directory of recruitment consultants. Almost 80 per cent said that who you
know had ceased to be more important than what you know when it comes to
getting a prized job.
So how about their own backgrounds: what sort of schools did they go to, for
instance? The fee-charging variety in 60 per cent of cases. As for
comprehensives, although the bulk were aged at most in their 40s, the tally
was 5 per cent.
