<HEADLINE>
FT  19 JUL 93 / Doubt raised on Sizewell C timing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GREEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NUCLEAR ELECTRIC, the state-owned generating company, has applied to
demolish a dock next to the site of the proposed Sizewell C nuclear power
station in Suffolk, suggesting that an application to build the Pounds 3.5bn
plant is still some way off.
The Pounds 6m dock was built three years ago to handle large loads for the
construction of Sizewell B. Nuclear Electric was hoping to use it when the
proposed twin-reactor Sizewell C plant was built.
In the continuing absence of permission from the Department of Trade and
Industry to submit a planning application for Sizewell C, officials have
bowed to local pressure to demolish the dock, which is causing erosion of
Sizewell beach.
The local authority fears that in the long term the effects could be felt
further along the coast.
Nuclear Electric had hoped to receive permission to submit a planning
application for Sizewell C after the coal review earlier this year.
