<HEADLINE>
FT  19 JUL 93 / Pledge over Taiwanese rail link
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DENNIS ENGBARTH
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TAIWAN officials at the weekend reaffirmed the government's determination to
build a USDollars 17bn (Pounds 11.3bn) high-speed railway despite a vote in
parliament on Friday to cut the project's budget for the fiscal year which
began on July 1, writes Dennis Engbarth in Taipei.
Legislators voted 58-49 in favour of cutting all NTDollars 9.44bn (Pounds
237m) in central government funding for the fiscal year 1994. The proposed
345km railway would cut transit time from Taipei to Kaoshiung to less than
two hours, from more than four hours now.
