the funds - a matter to be resolved in bilateral negotiations with the
European Commission.
Other subjects for discussion include efforts to tighten up on the export of
'dual use' technology; the new French initiative known as the Balladur plan
to protect minorities and foster stability in eastern Europe; the Uruguay
Round of multilateral trade talks, as well as stalled negotiations among the
12 to strengthen EC trade weapons; and the Commission's favourable, if
conditional, welcome of the applications of Malta and Cyprus to join the EC.
