magistrates have decided to keep holding Mr Gabriele Cagliari, the former
chairman of ENI, to continue their inquiries into the Enimont affair and
other matters.
Mr Cagliari has been in jail since March 4 on charges of illicit financing
of political parties and falsifying accounts.
